<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96656001125127></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96656001125127><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=96656001125127>Lay hands</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=96656001125127#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=461><span id= >Reklar</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 17th 8:53 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.89]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>A few bits of advice about LH.<br><br>While grouping, choose carefully whom you use your LH on. If you are in somewhere pleasant and safe like lguk, and the wiz is saying 'i'm trying to evac but i'm almost dead, and the tank says i'm almost dead from taunting things off the cannon, you've gotta choose whom to put it on.<br>If there is a primary healer, always communicate with them. it's heartbreaking to see someone get greater healed just as you hit that hotkey.<br>Also, tanks are good recipients of LH in situations like that, becuase they have the higher HP, so LH is more effective. You'll be healing a bit over your total HP, so putting it on a wiz whos not in dire straits is kinda a waste of over 500hp.<br><br>When soloing, choose your time wisely. if it's at all possible to root-med-heal, then do so. but by the same token, i have died while solo a couple of times from waiting *too* long to throw LH on, so don't do that :)<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
