<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9665461672450></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9665461672450><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=9665461672450>My humble thoughts on the paladin</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=9665461672450#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=395><span id= >MelftheElf</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>3 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 17th 5:02 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.62]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>A blank page encouraged me to pen a few thoughts on playing a paladin. I have played a high elf paladin exclusively since and including beta. I think I chose a paladin originally based on the belief a paladin would have the least down time of many character classes. I never factored in the additional time required to level based on the hybrid penalty.<br><br>Pro&#8217;s to playing a paladin<br><br>1. LoH will make you a few life long friends along the way<br>2. Your appearance is second to none at the highest levels<br>3. You have a very good weapon available at a fairly low level Ghoulbane<br>4. You do not spend large sums of money on spells<br>5. At lower levels you can solo fairly well<br>6. Playing a paladin has always been somewhat romantic for me<br><br><br>Con&#8217;s<br><br>1. Walk everywhere<br>2. Binding in cities only<br>3. At higher levels you take more damage then you can deal <br>4. The long spread between 41 and 49 when you basically get no spells no skills is anti climatic<br>5. Your buffs become almost useless in groups as other classes receive theirs<br>6. You can not solo<br>7. Clerics and even druids are better healers then you are<br>8. The soothe branch of spells are the most dangerous ones to try and pull mobs with<br>9. At higher levels, even in the undead zones nuking is a waste of mana<br>10. The pet classes replace the need of tanks at the highest level<br><br><br>All this said I chose a path less traveled by and that has made all the difference.<br><br>Melf Valiant High Elf Paladin lvl 46 Xegony<br> Still playing a paladin with honor and pride. <br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
