<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9668154331487></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9668154331487><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=9668154331487>RE: Soloing...</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=9668154331487#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Aug 20th 7:50 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[1.75]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>this is very lengthy, i apologize ahead of time<br><br>i solo'ed my way to 40 as a paladin, probably could have gone higher but i was too lazy to find the right place in kunark<br>1-9 is a gimme you can do anywhere<br><br>10-14 i spent mostly at the sisters camp in Lfay, was able to take 2 of them on at a time once i reached the teen lv's, before that there was usually someone else there id share the spawn with<br><br>14-16 i spent soloing the yard trash in unrest, (death beetles, zombies, and greater skele's)<br><br>17-23 i went back to antonica, these are the sad years when paladins suck, they dont get duel wield, and have a max dmg of 30 till you get lv 20 and double attack, so unless your twinked with ghoulbane, or a fast dly weapon, youll have to suck it in and find a group for a lv and a half like i did, after that i was high enough to go around soloing the bandits in hh, then while waiting for them to spawn, i killed an orc or two that the orc group (there will be one) missed<br><br>23-28/29 journey back to faydwer and solo'ed in MM castle, theres usually some groups there that keep the numbers down so you dont train, but by mid 20's its easy to solo even 2 familiars at the same time, just remember these important tactics<br>always ALWAYS use center to heal, it is about twice as mana efficient as light healing, and actually heals a tad faster<br>2nd, buy a high dmg weapon (like 2h silvery axe, they are affordable) and when you find a mob, pull it to a safe spot, and root it, then back off, and only attack it when your weapon delay is up, then back off again youll it it big, and he doesnt get multiple attacks in between your swings<br>(i also spent the low 20's soloing the orc chief camp in Lfay when MM was too crowded)<br><br>28/29-39 start saving up and buy yourself a ghoulbane (avg ~3000pp) and a decent shield, like cracked darkwood, or crested mm, if you want, you can also stock on some dex gear (my complete set gives quite a bit, but i didnt get it all till high 30's)<br>serpentine bracers are nice, black pearl jewelry is a must, as it gives agi AND dex, in large amount, 2 plat rings and a gold choker give +19 of each total<br>grotesque masks are easy to get as well<br><br>in unrest, youll be soloing in the house (obviously) if you dont have a ghoulbane, its ok, just use the same tactics as before (its also wise to get your evocation skill up, with our new max mana, you can solo something just by rooting and nuking it to death, but its not very efficient)<br>if you have your evocation high enough, theres a new tactic you can try if you want, if you still swingin that slow'ole 2h silvery, cast a ward undead in between swings<br>if you have ghoulbane, try to pull stuff outside where you can fear kite it (fear and just whack it till its down(, if you do it right, you get blue con exp and at the worst, have to heal yourself twice,<br>WARNING do NOT try to solo a festering hag unless you have ghoulbane, your bash is maxed, and you are lv 30 (so you can cast stun and interrupt its spells in addition to bash) unless you can pull it outside easily and fear kite it<br>hags give THE BEST exp, and once you hit mid thirties youll want these like mad, if you do it right, theyll maybe do a bubble of your life before you kill them, as they have little life<br>this is by far the best exp i ever got, continous blue con exp with little/no downtime<br>once you hit 34 you can start doing the blood pool room, id strongly advise against it untill you get a ghoulbane tho, at mid 30's i was able to do the entire room, 4 undead spawns (a terror will rarely spawn) and 2 mort fungi (optional, they are in pits and wont aggro you)<br>just remember, in ALL cases, if two mobs aggro you, simply root one and focus on the other, if a hag aggros, either kill her first or root her and run around a corner so she cant blast you<br>lv 40 i got mostly doing the ghost room with an enchanter (at least mid 30's) or a druid (slightly higher, as druids cant mezz)as stuff in the blood pool is mostly green to you by lv 39<br>its very easy, just tell the chanter to keep you hasted,<br>with the druid, just let him do what druids do, pretty simple<br><br>hope this helps a lot of you<br>sorry again for the length<br><br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
