	   <tr><td colspan=2>Sorry, I have to disagree<br>Paladins can take casters, and it's not all that difficult.&nbsp;&nbsp; Just calls for good timeing and a shield.   At lvl 30 you can take most blue cons with bash and stun (I Fought undead a very long time so have allways had a high Evocation, and i'm very much a 1hser, got my ghoulbane thanks to guildmates campin it at 31)<br>The thing is, if your going to take a caster, you have to stay right on top of it, waiting for it to start a spell.<br>When you do see that " @ begins to cast a spell" message, whack it with your shield (BASH).   If it isn't interrupted start castin stun on em and pray . . . you'll be able to take one or two blasts from anything blue no-sweat.   As long as you manage to knock the casters out of a few of their spells you'll be ok . . . it works for me anyways, might not work for everyone.<br>G'luck<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
