	   <tr><td colspan=2>It would also be advisable to know the quickest route to the zone/s. This may not be a problem in large areas such as the Karanas or the Commons, but it will be beneficial for when you are in dungeon zones. Lets face it. We do not have the advantage of GATING that the pure casters have, which some of them tend to do leaving the tank/s and other non-magic users to be sequentially taken out by a particularly nasty creature.<br><br>As for the lay of hands, it will always save us paladins when used properly, however it is also a judgement call whether to stick around and duke it out with the monster, as you never know when another will come along and butcher you as well.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
